climbs.name: Uncle Rico
climbs.fa: Jeremy Runyan, Clay Lippincott, Connie Lippincott

content.description: Start either direct by climbing through the overhanging start or you can by pass the overhang and enter from the left of the crack. This route has a little mix of hands, fist, to off width. Don't let the off width scare you away, it has good hands deep in the back.
content.protection: Take a normal rack from .75 to 4". Throw in a few additional #3's. Rap anchors are located at the top and left of the crack.
content.location: You cant miss this climb, it is the only visible crack on the south side of The Hood. Can be seen from the OHV trail.

climbs.name: El Naranjo
climbs.fa: Joey Jarrell, Murthy Tata, Manny Rangel

content.description: El Naranjo will be liked by some and not by others. It begins slightly overhanging and leaning with a well protected crux. Jam right foot in and skitter the left foot along the face. It's a fun tough route.
content.protection: doubles #2-4, (1) #5, med nut (#2 and nut work at the finish), draws, 60m
content.location: From Uncle Rico, walk right around the corner and up a few feet. We walked in from the East and left cairns from the loop trail across/north from Ashley's Block.

content.description: 60 to 70 foot high dome with huge blocks on top of it. The south side is in direct sunlight for most of the day.
